mods.title: 4Real Module 01 - Crop destruction
mods.description:
Adds crop destruction to all wheels except care wheels or thin/narrow wheels.

Update 1.0.2.0 - Grass will be reduced to second to last growth state which is still mowable.
- Caruelle Nicolas Stilla 460 and New Holland SP.400F are properly detected as using care wheels, will not destroy crops anymore.
Previous Update 1.0.1.0 - Oilseed radish is not destroyed anymore.

mods.title: 4Real Module 02 - Tire Dirt
mods.description:
Adds more dynamic dirt to tires. Dirt is applied separately on each wheel depending on the ground.

Update 1.0.1.0: - Increased time it takes to dirty/clean wheels. Wheels are not cleaned as much anymore on roads or grass.

mods.title: 4Real Module 03 - Ground Response
mods.description: Adds more advanced terrain properties. Tires will sink into the soil depending on the type and weather, wheels respond more dynamically to rough ground and slip more on wet soil.

currentGameplayHints: You can buy sheep, cows and pigs directly from the livestock dealer.
Cattle trucks allow you to transport newly acquired animals to their respective enclosures. For a fee, the livestock dealer can transport them for you.
You must take care of your animals: all of them need food and water, and some require you to periodically change their bedding by using a straw blower.
You can either make square bales or round bales.
After making bales, you can use an automatic bale loader to gather them quickly.
You need different bale loaders for square or round bales.
Chaff can mainly be gained by harvesting corn with a forage harvester. You can use a forage harvester in conjunction with a header and a trailer.
You can also make chaff out of wheat, barley, canola or grass.
Chaff cannot be sold. You need it to produce silage.
If you want your cows to produce milk, you have to feed them regularly. They eat grass, hay, silage and Total Mixed Ration (TMR).
Well-fed cows not only produce milk but slurry as well, which is collected either in a slurry tank or pit.
Adding straw bedding to the cow stable results in manure. Manure can be used to fertilize your fields or to improve the income of the greenhouse.
After a harvest you can use a cultivator to prepare the field directly for the next sowing without having to plow it.
But after the third harvest, you will need to plow the field again, or it will yield 10% less crops.
Keep in mind that only a plow allows you to define new field dimensions.
You can directly make silage from a hay bale by using a bale wrapper.
To earn money, you need to sell what you produce (crops, animals and their products, wood).
It is recommended to always start working a field from its shortest side. This will save you unnecessary turns.
During hail or rain you can't harvest your crops and have to wait until the weather clears up.
If a vehicle or tool is stuck, you can reset it on the map overview screen.
100 gold nuggets are spread all over Goldcrest Valley. Can you find them all?
Don't know how to do something? Check the help section in the pause menu.
Change your environment! You can transform a forest into fields if you want to: cut down the trees, remove the stumps and use a plow to create a field.
Sheep don't require much. If they have enough water and grass from the pasture, they will produce wool which can be picked up and sold at the town's spinnery.
Your vehicles age over time which slowly increases their maintenance costs per day.
The tree harvesters can only cut fir trees. But they process them very quickly.
You can't customize a leased vehicle.
If your vehicle is dirty, use a pressure washer to clean it.
Some tippers allow you to attach other tippers behind them.
Trees can be cut with a chainsaw or a tree harvester. They should be debranched and cut into logs before they're sold.
Note that you can carry around small pieces of wood by hand as long as they are not too heavy.
The maintenance cost of vehicles and tools increases with age. Old equipment should be sold when it has outlasted its usefulness.
If your front loader is carrying something heavy, you can attach a weight to the tractor's rear to balance it out.
There are many activities that can earn you achievements. Can you unlock them all?
You can increase the yield of your harvest by fertilizing and spraying your fields after seeding.
Change your environment! You can extend and merge your fields with a plow if you want to.
Cows eat grass, silage or total mixed ration (TMR). They also need water and their stable requires a straw bedding. Happy cows produce milk, slurry and manure.
Sheep, cows and pigs can be purchased at the livestock dealer. Pick them up with a animal trailer or have them delivered.
Be it corn, grain, soy beans, canola, potatoes, sugar beets or a feed mixture - pigs can be fed nearly everything.
If you drive your machines to the vehicle shop and sell them in the marked area, you receive more of the original purchase price than if you sell them through your garage.
If your animals are supplied with water, food and a clean stable, you can soon expect offspring.
The vehicle shop occasionally announces sales where you can get certain machines for a reduced price.
After sowing a field, you can improve the harvest by fertilizing it. You should fertilize a field three times before harvesting it.
Each time you fertilize a field, it yields 30% more crops. Thus fertilizing a field three times yields a total of 90% more crops.
You can fertilize a field with fertilizer, manure or slurry.
To work a field, you have to buy it first.
Each field not in your possession has a buy symbol nearby. If you activate this symbol, you get the option to purchase the field.
Fields already in your possession are marked with green numbers on the map.
On the finance screen, you can see all income and expenditures for the current day and the previous four days. The loan you have from the bank is also displayed.
If you need more money urgently, you can borrow some from the bank in increments of $CURRENCY_SYMBOL5000.
However, at the end of each day, you have to pay excessive interest on the loans you have taken out. You can pay back your loans at any time.
Selling wood is a profitable business and can be a welcome change from regular work in the fields. Every tree on the map can be cut and sold.
You can use a crane to haul tree trunks into a trailer.
Both the length of a piece and its suitability for processing (the less curvature the better) determines the price you can get for it.
Grass is cut with a mower which is usually attached to a tractor. Afterwards, you can use a tedder to turn the cut grass around, thus making it dry faster.
To make grass collecting easier, it is recommended to arrange it into rows by using a windrower. Grass can be collected with a loader wagon or turned into bales with a baler.
There is also the option to use a chopper which turns grass into chaff.
When crops are ready for harvesting, you can use a harvester.
A harvester needs a header. Certain types of crop require special headers.
Once the harvester's tank is full, you can unload it into a trailer.
Most of the fields on the map are owned by other farmers controlled by the computer. They take care of their fields but are always in need of assistance.
To start a job for them, activate the symbol next to their field. The farmer will provide you with specific tools in order to do the job.
Note that each time you complete a job, your relationship with the farmer improves. The more you work for them, the cheaper the price of their field becomes.
You can place beehouses, solar panels or wind energy converters on the map and use them as regular sources of income.
Greenhouses let you produce tomatoes or lettuce. In order to earn money, you need to fill the water tank on the side of the greenhouse by using a water trailer.
You can improve the income of a greenhouse by filling its wooden box with manure.
Plowing allows you to prepare the soil before sowing. You can also use a cultivator to prepare the field.
Note that a plowed field yields 10% more crops. This benefit only lasts for three harvests and then you need to plow the field again.
You can also use plows to create new fields.
To harvest potatoes, you first need to remove the foliage with a haulm cutter and then dig them up with a potato harvester.
You can store potatoes by heaping them up in one of your farm's storage shelters.
Note that beet harvesting works in the same way as potato harvesting.
When a field is ready for sowing, you can use a potato planter to make a potato field.
Just like for other sowing machines, you can fill a potato planter when you are near a seed bag.
Note that you can also use potatoes from your last harvest for the planter.
The prices of all sellable commodities change daily and act in accordance to supply and demand.
You can influence the prices by deciding what you want to deliver and how much of it.
This also means that prices for commodities you hardly ever sell go up much faster.
There are six types of crop: wheat, barley, canola, sunflowers, soybeans and corn.
There are two types of root crop: potatoes and sugar beets.
Oilseed radish is a special type of root crop. You plant it to improve the yield of the next harvest.
On the map, there is a vehicle shop where you can buy vehicles and tools. Or you can access the shop whenever you want.
The machines are split up into several categories which you can toggle through.
You can also browse the machines by brand.
Most vehicles can be customized when bought. Each of them has different customization possibilities.
To customize a vehicle later, you can drive it into the marked area next to the shop and then activate the nearby symbol.
When leasing or buying a vehicle, the price is linked to how much customization you install on the vehicle.
If you want to try new vehicles or tools, you have the possibility to lease them instead of buying them.
In order to do so, you can go to the shop and press the lease button instead of the buy button.
You will be asked to pay a starting fee and then you will be charged by the hour. The price you pay is linked to the customizations you select.
Every so often, the vehicle shop puts individual machines on sale.
Sales are temporary, thus it is a good idea to visit the shop frequently and see if there is something available for less.

On rare occasions the vehicle shop comes up with a brand sale which lowers the prices of all machines of a certain brand for a short time. If a brand sale happens, you will receive a message to make sure you don't miss it.

To turn chaff into silage, you need to dump it into a silo (either next to the cow stable or at the biogas plant). Once the silo is at least 10% full, you can compact the heap by driving over it repeatedly with a tractor.
Afterwards, you can cover the silo and start the fermenting process.
The resulting silage can be picked up with a front loader equipped with a shovel or a silage fork and dumped into a mixer-wagon or directly into a feeding trough.
After preparing a field, you can sow it using a sowing machine.
A sowing machine needs seeds. You can find seed bags at your farm or buy new ones in the shop.
Note that a sowing machine can't plant all types of crops.
When you harvest wheat or barley, you are allowed to create straw swath with the harvester.
Straw swath can be packed into bales by using a baler. Alternatively, straw can be picked up by loading wagons.
Straw can be sold directly, used as bedding for cows or used as a component for total mixed ration (TMR).
Your cows always produce milk but you can improve their productivity by feeding them well. The best food you can give your cow is total mixed ration (TMR).
Total mixed ration is produced by mixing hay, straw and silage in a mixer-wagon.
Loading the bales first and the silage afterwards makes it easier to determine how much silage is necessary to achieve a perfect mixture.
Besides regular vehicles you can also steer trains. You can use them to load a lot more of your production and move it quickly across the map.
Use cranes to load or unload wood from the trains.
Note that you can't transport animals by train. Use the cattle truck instead.
New trees do not just pop up by themselves. They need to be planted with a specialized planting machine. The shop can provide you with seedling pallets.
You can also crush any logs into wood chips by using a wood chipper and deliver them either to the sawmill or to a biomass heating plant where they are converted into heat.
After cutting down a tree, the remaining stump can be removed with a stump cutter.
